# CS 408 Lab 7

## Overview

This project is mainly to practice responsive layouts when building a webpage. These include positioning, dynamic units, flex and grid layouts, etc.

## Usage

- When viewing the webpage, be sure to maximize and minimize the display window to experience responsive elements.

## Running

1. Open the index.html file in your preferred text editor or IDE.
2. Run your preferred live server to view the html file.
   - i.e. VSCode Live Server or Live Preview plugin, IntelliJ IDE plugin, Vim plugin, etc.
3. [Optional] Once your server is started, you may open it in the browser if you prefer it.

## Sources and Credits

- Media Queries: <https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/CSS/CSS_layout/Media_queries>
